                <h1>Understanding Background Check Disclosure: A Quick Guide</h1>
                <p>Background check disclosure is a legal requirement that informs candidates when an employer intends to conduct a background check. This ensures transparency and allows individuals to understand their rights. Employers must obtain written consent before proceeding and provide candidates with access to the results, promoting fairness in hiring practices.</p>
